				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question about the Thurg Ring Quests<a name="38960"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 7 04 10:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Why fight the mobs?  
<br />

<br />
This will require you to have a friend that can root or a friend that can mem wipe.
<br />

<br />
Just agro Corbin right after the ambush spawns and run the opposite direction you came in on.  Then circle back around to the Coldain camp.  Then you have 2 options
<br />

<br />
1.  If your using your rooting partner, root Corbin just outside the Coldain camp.  Both log out and back in.  Corbin will take about 2 minutes to resume his walk.
<br />
  
<br />
2.  If your useing your mem wipe partner mem wipe Corbin just outside the Coldain camp.  After about 2 minutes he will resume the walk.
<br />

<br />
Ive done this both ways with a Druid and a Necro.
<br />

<br />
BTW all the ambush mobs will wonder over to the Ry'Gorr fort wiping the coldains in the huts by the Ry'Gorr fort.  So this tacktic should be used with care.  If you run just after doing the turn in for the Note you can get the ambush mobs before they wipe the Coldain.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now that I'm level 65, I just agro Corbin and run him over by the Coldain camp and Fading Memories. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  Wait for him to finish his walk and do the turn in for the Note.  Then I'll go kill the ambush mobs as they wander between the Ry'Gorr fort and the ambush spot.  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
